[0.001, "o", "; interesting side-effects depending on your application and web server.\r"]
[0.032, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[?1c\u001b[?25h\u001b[?0c"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b7\u001b[2;65r\u001b8\u001bM\u001b[1;67r\u001b[2;1H"]
[0.001, "o", "; Turning on this setting and managing its maximum buffer size can yield some\r"]
[0.033, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[?1c\u001b[?25h\u001b[?0c"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b7\u001b[2;64r\u001b8\u001bM\u001b[1;67r\u001b[2;1H; will send that data in chunks of roughly the size you specify.\r"]
[0.034, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[?1c\u001b[?25h\u001b[?0c"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b7\u001b[2;64r\u001b8\u001bM\u001b[1;67r\u001b[2;1H"]
[0.001, "o", "; data to the client. If your application's output exceeds this setting, PHP\r"]
